README.md Project documentation and getting started guide
The main documentation for treex, explaining what it does and how to use it

LICENSE MIT License
Standard MIT license for open source distribution

.github/workflows/go.yml GitHub Actions CI workflow
Runs tests and linting on pull requests and pushes to main

cmd/treex/main.go Main entry point
Bootstrap code that initializes the CLI and runs the root command

cmd/treex/cmd/ CLI command implementations
Contains all the cobra command definitions and CLI logic

pkg/app/ Application orchestration layer
Core business logic that coordinates between parsing, building, and rendering

pkg/tree/ Tree building and filtering
Handles directory traversal, tree construction, and view mode filtering

pkg/info/ .info file parsing
Parser for reading and interpreting .info annotation files

pkg/format/ Output formatting system
Extensible rendering system supporting multiple output formats (color, json, markdown, etc.)

pkg/tui/ Terminal UI components
Tree rendering logic for terminal output with colors and styling

pkg/maketree/ Tree structure creation
Creates file system structures from tree representations

scripts/ Development and build scripts
Build, test, lint, and release automation scripts

docs/ Additional documentation
Development guides, installation instructions, and format specifications

example/ Example projects
Sample directory structures with .info files demonstrating treex usage

test-tabstop/ Test fixtures
Test data for tab stop alignment in tree rendering